ries should pass\",\n518-        \"Run vendor/bin/pest — all tests pass with zero failures\"\n519-      ],\n520-      \"priority\": 32,\n521:      \"passes\": false"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f33b1984-41c7-44b2-8f5f-4c154dd0be88","uuid":"4927ab17-2708-4d5e-9436-2ec09ca19648","tool_use_result":{"mode":"content","numFiles":0,"filenames":[],"content":"13-        \"phpunit.xml (or pest equivalent) configured for the tests/ directory\",\n14-        \"Directory structure created: src/Contracts/, src/Stores/, src/Models/, src/Concerns/, src/Events/, src/Facades/, src/Middleware/, src/Commands/, src/DTOs/, src/Documents/, tests/Feature/\",\n15-        \"vendor/bin/pest runs with zero tests and no errors\"\n16-      ],\n17-      \"priority\": 1,\n18:      \"passes\": false\n--\n29-        \"Migration create_boundaries_table: boundaries table with id(), string('scope')-\\u003eunique(), json('max_permissions'), timestamps()\",\n30-        \"Migrations are publishable via the service provider's boot() method using $this-\\u003epublishesMigrations()\",\n31-        \"All migrations use anonymous classes (return new class extends Migration)\"\n32-      ],\n33-      \"priority\": 2,\n34:      \"passes\": false\n--\n44-        \"src/Models/Assignment.php — model with $table = 'assignments', fillable: ['subject_type', 'subject_id', 'role_id', 'scope'], has a subject() morphTo relationship, belongs to Role\",\n45-        \"src/Models/Boundary.php — model with $table = 'boundaries', fillable: ['scope', 'max_permissions'], cast max_permissions to array\",\n46-        \"All models have full PHP 8.4 type hints on properties and return types on methods\"\n47-      ],\n48-      \"priority\": 3,\n49:      \"passes\": false\n--\n65-        \"src/Contracts/DocumentExporter.php — interface with method: export(?string $scope = null): PolicyDocument\",\n66-        \"All interfaces are in DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Contracts\\\\ namespace\",\n67-        \"All method signatures have full PHP 8.4 type hints and return types\"\n68-      ],\n69-      \"priority\": 4,\n70:      \"passes\": false\n--\n81-        \"src/DTOs/ValidationResult.php — readonly class with public properties: bool $valid, array $errors (string[])\",\n82-        \"All DTOs are in DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\DTOs\\\\ namespace\",\n83-        \"All DTOs use PHP 8.4 readonly classes with typed constructor parameters\"\n84-      ],\n85-      \"priority\": 5,\n86:      \"passes\": false\n--\n103-        \"Deep verb matching: posts.delete.* matches posts.delete.own and posts.delete.any — returns true\",\n104-        \"Deny prefix is NOT handled by matcher — deny logic (! prefix) is the evaluator's responsibility. Matcher only compares raw permission strings without the ! prefix\",\n105-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/WildcardMatcherTest.php covering all cases above\"\n106-      ],\n107-      \"priority\": 6,\n108:      \"passes\": false\n--\n118-        \"If $scope is a Model with a toScope() method (i.e., uses Scopeable trait), calls toScope() and returns the result\",\n119-        \"If $scope is an unsupported type, throws \\\\InvalidArgumentException\",\n120-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/ModelScopeResolverTest.php covering null, string, Scopeable model, and invalid input\"\n121-      ],\n122-      \"priority\": 7,\n123:      \"passes\": false\n--\n135-        \"Events are dispatched using Event::dispatch(), not the event() helper\",\n136-        \"Uses Model::query() instead of DB:: facade\",\n137-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/EloquentPermissionStoreTest.php covering register (single, array, idempotent), remove (with cascade), all (with and without prefix), exists\"\n138-      ],\n139-      \"priority\": 8,\n140:      \"passes\": false\n--\n152-        \"permissionsFor(string $roleId): returns an array of permission ID strings for the role (from role_permissions table)\",\n153-        \"Uses Event::dispatch() for events, Model::query() for queries\",\n154-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/EloquentRoleStoreTest.php covering save (create, update, sync permissions), remove (normal, system-protected), find, all, permissionsFor\"\n155-      ],\n156-      \"priority\": 9,\n157:      \"passes\": false\n--\n169-        \"subjectsInScope(string $scope, ?string $roleId = null): returns all assignments in the scope. If $roleId is provided, also filters by role\",\n170-        \"Uses Event::dispatch() for events, Model::query() for queries\",\n171-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/EloquentAssignmentStoreTest.php covering assign (new, idempotent), revoke, forSubject, forSubjectInScope, subjectsInScope (with and without roleId)\"\n172-      ],\n173-      \"priority\": 10,\n174:      \"passes\": false\n--\n184-        \"find(string $scope): returns the Boundary model or null\",\n185-        \"Uses Model::query() for queries\",\n186-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/EloquentBoundaryStoreTest.php covering set (create, update), remove, find (exists, not exists)\"\n187-      ],\n188-      \"priority\": 11,\n189:      \"passes\": false\n--\n205-        \"All events are in DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Events\\\\ namespace\",\n206-        \"All events use constructor promotion for properties\",\n207-        \"No event extends any base class (plain classes, not Eloquent events)\"\n208-      ],\n209-      \"priority\": 12,\n210:      \"passes\": false\n--\n220-        \"explain(...) — returns an EvaluationTrace DTO with the full resolution chain. If config('policy-engine.explain') is false, throws \\\\RuntimeException\",\n221-        \"effectivePermissions(string $subjectType, string|int $subjectId, ?string $scope = null) — returns array of all permission strings the subject is effectively granted (after deny filtering) in the given scope (or globally if null)\",\n222-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/DefaultEvaluatorTest.php covering: basic allow, basic deny, deny-wins-over-allow, wildcard grants, scoped evaluation, boundary enforcement (permission within boundary, permission outside boundary), no-assignment-means-deny, explain output structure\"\n223-      ],\n224-      \"priority\": 13,\n225:      \"passes\": false\n--\n239-        \"explain() and effectivePermissions() delegate to inner evaluator (no caching on these)\",\n240-        \"src/Listeners/InvalidatePermissionCache.php — a listener class that flushes relevant cache keys. Register it to listen for: AssignmentCreated, AssignmentRevoked, RoleUpdated, RoleDeleted, PermissionDeleted. On each event, flush the affected subject's cache keys (or flush all policy-engine cache keys if the affected subject cannot be determined, e.g., role changes affect all subjects with that role)\",\n241-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/CachedEvaluatorTest.php covering: cache hit behavior, cache miss behavior, cache invalidation on assignment change, cache invalidation on role change, cache disabled config\"\n242-      ],\n243-      \"priority\": 14,\n244:      \"passes\": false\n--\n261-        \"explain(string $permission, mixed $scope = null): EvaluationTrace — resolves scope, delegates to Evaluator::explain()\",\n262-        \"All methods resolve contracts from the container via app() — the trait holds no logic, only delegation\",\n263-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/HasPermissionsTraitTest.php using a test User model, covering: canDo/cannotDo, assign/revoke, assignments/assignmentsFor, roles/rolesFor, effectivePermissions\"\n264-      ],\n265-      \"priority\": 15,\n266:      \"passes\": false\n--\n276-        \"members(): Collection — delegates to AssignmentStore::subjectsInScope($this-\\u003etoScope()), returns the collection of assignments\",\n277-        \"membersWithRole(string $roleId): Collection — delegates to AssignmentStore::subjectsInScope($this-\\u003etoScope(), $roleId)\",\n278-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/ScopeableTraitTest.php using a test Group model, covering: toScope output format, members, membersWithRole\"\n279-      ],\n280-      \"priority\": 16,\n281:      \"passes\": false\n--\n295-        \"export(?string $scope = null): string — delegates to DocumentExporter::export() then DocumentParser::serialize()\",\n296-        \"exportToFile(string $path, ?string $scope = null): void — same as export() but writes result to file\",\n297-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/PrimitivesFacadeTest.php covering: permissions registration, role creation with grant chaining, boundary setting, import from string, export\"\n298-      ],\n299-      \"priority\": 17,\n300:      \"passes\": false\n--\n308-        \"src/Middleware/RoleMiddleware.php — middleware class with handle(Request $request, Closure $next, string $role, ?string $scopeParam = null). Gets the authenticated user. Resolves scope same as CanDoMiddleware. Checks if user has the required role in scope by querying AssignmentStore::forSubjectInScope() (or forSubject() if no scope) and checking if any assignment has the required role_id. If no matching assignment, aborts with 403. If found, passes to $next\",\n309-        \"Both middleware are registered in the service provider with aliases can_do and role\",\n310-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/MiddlewareTest.php covering: can_do allows, can_do denies (403), can_do with scope parameter, role allows, role denies (403), unauthenticated user (401 or redirect)\"\n311-      ],\n312-      \"priority\": 18,\n313:      \"passes\": false\n--\n323-        \"Directives are registered in the service provider's boot() method via Blade::if()\",\n324-        \"If no user is authenticated, all directives evaluate to false (never throws)\",\n325-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/BladeDirectivesTest.php covering: canDo renders content when allowed, canDo hides content when denied, cannotDo inverse behavior, hasRole with and without scope, unauthenticated user sees nothing\"\n326-      ],\n327-      \"priority\": 19,\n328:      \"passes\": false\n--\n338-        \"validate(string $content): ValidationResult — validates JSON structure without importing. Checks: valid JSON, version field exists, permissions is array of strings (if present), roles entries have id, name, permissions keys (if present), assignments entries have subject and role keys (if present), boundaries entries have scope and max_permissions keys (if present). Returns ValidationResult with valid = true or valid = false with error messages\",\n339-        \"All sections of the document (permissions, roles, assignments, boundaries) are optional — a document with only roles is valid\",\n340-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/JsonDocumentParserTest.php covering: parse valid document, parse partial document (roles only), parse invalid JSON, serialize round-trip, validate valid document, validate invalid document\"\n341-      ],\n342-      \"priority\": 20,\n343:      \"passes\": false\n--\n351-        \"Constructor accepts: PermissionStore, RoleStore, AssignmentStore, BoundaryStore\",\n352-[Omitted long context line]\n353-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/DefaultDocumentImporterTest.php covering: full import, merge mode, replace mode, dry run (no DB changes), skip assignments, validation warnings, round-trip with exporter\"\n354-      ],\n355-      \"priority\": 21,\n356:      \"passes\": false\n--\n364-        \"Constructor accepts: PermissionStore, RoleStore, AssignmentStore, BoundaryStore\",\n365-[Omitted long context line]\n366-        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/DefaultDocumentExporterTest.php covering: export all, export scoped, export empty state, round-trip with importer\"\n367-      ],\n368-      \"priority\": 22,\n369:      \"passes\": false\n--\n378-        \"src/Commands/ListAssignmentsCommand.php — signature: primitives:assignments {subject?} {--scope=}. If subject argument is provided, lists assignments for that subject (ex