{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement US-001: Create package scaffolding for `dynamik-dev/laravel-policy-engine`.\n\nThis is a Laravel package (NOT an application). The working directory is `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **composer.json** exists with:\n   - name: `dynamik-dev/laravel-policy-engine`\n   - PHP `^8.4` requirement\n   - Laravel `^11.0|^12.0` requirement\n   - `pestphp/pest` as dev dependency\n   - PSR-4 autoload mapping `DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\` to `src/`\n   - PSR-4 autoload-dev mapping `DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Tests\\\\` to `tests/`\n   - `extra.laravel.providers` with `DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\PolicyEngineServiceProvider`\n\n2. **src/PolicyEngineServiceProvider.php** — skeleton class extending `Illuminate\\Support\\ServiceProvider` with empty `register()` and `boot()` methods. Full PHP 8.4 type hints and return types.\n\n3. **config/policy-engine.php** — returns the configuration array:\n```php\nreturn [\n    'cache' => [\n        'enabled' => true,\n        'store' => env('POLICY_ENGINE_CACHE_STORE', 'default'),\n        'ttl' => 60 * 60,\n    ],\n    'protect_system_roles' => true,\n    'log_denials' => true,\n    'explain' => env('POLICY_ENGINE_EXPLAIN', false),\n    'document_format' => 'json',\n];\n```\n\n4. **phpunit.xml** configured for the `tests/` directory with Pest.\n\n5. **Directory structure** created with `.gitkeep` files:\n   - `src/Contracts/`\n   - `src/Stores/`\n   - `src/Models/`\n   - `src/Concerns/`\n   - `src/Events/`\n   - `src/Facades/`\n   - `src/Middleware/`\n   - `src/Commands/`\n   - `src/DTOs/`\n   - `src/Documents/`\n   - `tests/Feature/`\n\n6. **vendor/bin/pest runs with zero tests and no errors**\n\n## Style Rules (from CLAUDE.md)\n- Full PHP 8.4+ type hints and return types on every method\n- No `compact()` — explicit arrays only\n- Package namespace: `DynamikDev\\PolicyEngine\\`\n\n## Important\n- This is a Laravel PACKAGE, not an app. composer.json should have `type: \"library\"`.\n- Make sure the `Pest.php` file exists at `tests/Pest.php` for Pest configuration.\n- After creating all files, run `composer install` and then `vendor/bin/pest` to verify it works.\n- Do NOT use `orchestra/testbench` unless needed for pest to work — if you do need it, add it as a dev dependency.\n- For pest to work in a package context, you will likely need `orchestra/testbench` with `pestphp/pest-plugin-laravel`.\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017mgCWbgqnEQk9yq1dYKH95","session_id":"f33b1984-41c7-44b2-8f5f-4c154dd0be88","uuid":"31770f5d-fd52-40bb-877e-13134f65b254"}
