{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AjujfkDFZRhS9dSLeoRkWP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## Codebase Patterns\n     2→- Use `orchestra/testbench` + `pestphp/pest-plugin-laravel` for package testing\n     3→- Tests extend `DynamikDev\\PolicyEngine\\Tests\\TestCase` which registers the service provider\n     4→- Config key is `policy-engine`, env prefix is `POLICY_ENGINE_`\n     5→- All PHP files use `declare(strict_types=1)`\n     6→- Package namespace: `DynamikDev\\PolicyEngine\\`\n     7→- Use anonymous migration classes (`return new class extends Migration`)\n     8→- Run `vendor/bin/pint --dirty` after modifying PHP files\n     9→- Use `vendor/bin/pest` for testing\n    10→\n    11→---\n    12→\n    13→## 2026-02-26 - US-001\n    14→- What was implemented: Package scaffolding — composer.json, service provider, config, phpunit.xml, Pest setup, and full directory structure\n    15→- Files changed:\n    16→  - `composer.json` — package definition with all dependencies\n    17→  - `src/PolicyEngineServiceProvider.php` — skeleton service provider\n    18→  - `config/policy-engine.php` — configuration array\n    19→  - `phpunit.xml` — test configuration\n    20→  - `tests/Pest.php` — Pest configuration\n    21→  - `tests/TestCase.php` — base test case with testbench\n    22→  - `.gitignore` — standard ignores\n    23→  - `.gitkeep` files in all src/ subdirectories and tests/Feature/\n    24→- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n    25→  - Package testing requires `orchestra/testbench` and `pestphp/pest-plugin-laravel` as dev dependencies\n    26→  - The TestCase.php needs to register the service provider via `getPackageProviders()`\n    27→  - `vendor/bin/pest` runs cleanly with zero tests and no errors on PHP 8.5.2\n    28→  - The service provider merges config in `register()` and publishes it in `boot()`\n    29→---\n    30→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce4d2e8c-11e0-48e3-8ef5-8ea123e4d07a","uuid":"08b31763-b7ba-496f-804b-af960f840d92","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/.chief/prds/policy-engine-1/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- Use `orchestra/testbench` + `pestphp/pest-plugin-laravel` for package testing\n- Tests extend `DynamikDev\\PolicyEngine\\Tests\\TestCase` which registers the service provider\n- Config key is `policy-engine`, env prefix is `POLICY_ENGINE_`\n- All PHP files use `declare(strict_types=1)`\n- Package namespace: `DynamikDev\\PolicyEngine\\`\n- Use anonymous migration classes (`return new class extends Migration`)\n- Run `vendor/bin/pint --dirty` after modifying PHP files\n- Use `vendor/bin/pest` for testing\n\n---\n\n## 2026-02-26 - US-001\n- What was implemented: Package scaffolding — composer.json, service provider, config, phpunit.xml, Pest setup, and full directory structure\n- Files changed:\n  - `composer.json` — package definition with all dependencies\n  - `src/PolicyEngineServiceProvider.php` — skeleton service provider\n  - `config/policy-engine.php` — configuration array\n  - `phpunit.xml` — test configuration\n  - `tests/Pest.php` — Pest configuration\n  - `tests/TestCase.php` — base test case with testbench\n  - `.gitignore` — standard ignores\n  - `.gitkeep` files in all src/ subdirectories and tests/Feature/\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - Package testing requires `orchestra/testbench` and `pestphp/pest-plugin-laravel` as dev dependencies\n  - The TestCase.php needs to register the service provider via `getPackageProviders()`\n  - `vendor/bin/pest` runs cleanly with zero tests and no errors on PHP 8.5.2\n  - The service provider merges config in `register()` and publishes it in `boot()`\n---\n","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":30}}}
