{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LJy8bmrGPuRR4n3mgvbTE6","type":"tool_result","content":"   300→   300→   300→      \"priority\": 17,\n   301→   301→   301→      \"passes\": false\n   302→   302→   302→    },\n   303→   303→   303→    {\n   304→   304→   304→      \"id\": \"US-018\",\n   305→   305→   305→      \"title\": \"Implement middleware\",\n   306→   306→   306→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need can_do and role middleware so routes can be protected with permission and role checks.\",\n   307→   307→   307→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   308→   308→   308→        \"src/Middleware/CanDoMiddleware.php — middleware class with handle(Request $request, Closure $next, string $permission, ?string $scopeParam = null). Gets the authenticated user via $request-\\u003euser(). If $scopeParam is provided, resolves the scope from route parameters: $request-\\u003eroute($scopeParam). The route parameter value will be a model (via route model binding) or a string — pass it through ScopeResolver. Calls $user-\\u003ecanDo($permission, scope: $resolvedScope). If denied, aborts with 403. If allowed, passes to $next\",\n   309→   309→   309→        \"src/Middleware/RoleMiddleware.php — middleware class with handle(Request $request, Closure $next, string $role, ?string $scopeParam = null). Gets the authenticated user. Resolves scope same as CanDoMiddleware. Checks if user has the required role in scope by querying AssignmentStore::forSubjectInScope() (or forSubject() if no scope) and checking if any assignment has the required role_id. If no matching assignment, aborts with 403. If found, passes to $next\",\n   310→   310→   310→        \"Both middleware are registered in the service provider with aliases can_do and role\",\n   311→   311→   311→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/MiddlewareTest.php covering: can_do allows, can_do denies (403), can_do with scope parameter, role allows, role denies (403), unauthenticated user (401 or redirect)\"\n   312→   312→   312→      ],\n   313→   313→   313→      \"priority\": 18,\n   314→   314→   314→      \"passes\": false\n   315→   315→   315→    },\n   316→   316→   316→    {\n   317→   317→   317→      \"id\": \"US-019\",\n   318→   318→   318→      \"title\": \"Implement Blade directives\",\n   319→   319→   319→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need Blade directives so views can conditionally render based on permissions and roles.\",\n   320→   320→   320→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   321→   321→   321→        \"@canDo('permission', $scope) / @endCanDo — compiles to a PHP if-block that calls auth()-\\u003euser()-\\u003ecanDo('permission', $scope). The second argument ($scope) is optional\",\n   322→   322→   322→        \"@cannotDo('permission', $scope) / @endCannotDo — compiles to the negation\",\n   323→   323→   323→        \"@hasRole('role', $scope) / @endHasRole — compiles to check if the user has the role assignment in the given scope. Uses AssignmentStore to check\",\n   324→   324→   324→        \"Directives are registered in the service provider's boot() method via Blade::if()\",\n   325→   325→   325→        \"If no user is authenticated, all directives evaluate to false (never throws)\",\n   326→   326→   326→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/BladeDirectivesTest.php covering: canDo renders content when allowed, canDo hides content when denied, cannotDo inverse behavior, hasRole with and without scope, unauthenticated user sees nothing\"\n   327→   327→   327→      ],\n   328→   328→   328→      \"priority\": 19,\n   329→   329→   329→      \"passes\": false\n   330→   330→   330→    },\n   331→   331→   331→    {\n   332→   332→   332→      \"id\": \"US-020\",\n   333→   333→   333→      \"title\": \"Implement JsonDocumentParser\",\n   334→   334→   334→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a JSON document parser so policy documents can be parsed from and serialized to JSON strings.\",\n   335→   335→   335→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   336→   336→   336→        \"src/Documents/JsonDocumentParser.php implements DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Contracts\\\\DocumentParser\",\n   337→   337→   337→        \"parse(string $content): PolicyDocument — decodes JSON string, validates structure, returns a PolicyDocument DTO. Throws \\\\InvalidArgumentException if JSON is invalid\",\n   338→   338→   338→        \"serialize(PolicyDocument $document): string — encodes the DTO to a pretty-printed JSON string (JSON_PRETTY_PRINT | JSON_UNESCAPED_SLASHES)\",\n   339→   339→   339→        \"validate(string $content): ValidationResult — validates JSON structure without importing. Checks: valid JSON, version field exists, permissions is array of strings (if present), roles entries have id, name, permissions keys (if present), assignments entries have subject and role keys (if present), boundaries entries have scope and max_permissions keys (if present). Returns ValidationResult with valid = true or valid = false with error messages\",\n   340→   340→   340→        \"All sections of the document (permissions, roles, assignments, boundaries) are optional — a document with only roles is valid\",\n   341→   341→   341→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/JsonDocumentParserTest.php covering: parse valid document, parse partial document (roles only), parse invalid JSON, serialize round-trip, validate valid document, validate invalid document\"\n   342→   342→   342→      ],\n   343→   343→   343→      \"priority\": 20,\n   344→   344→   344→      \"passes\": false\n   345→   345→   345→    },\n   346→   346→   346→    {\n   347→   347→   347→      \"id\": \"US-021\",\n   348→   348→   348→      \"title\": \"Implement DefaultDocumentImporter\",\n   349→   349→   349→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a document importer so parsed policy documents can be applied to the stores.\",\n   350→   350→   350→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   351→   351→   351→        \"src/Documents/DefaultDocumentImporter.php implements DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Contracts\\\\DocumentImporter\",\n   352→   352→   352→        \"Constructor accepts: PermissionStore, RoleStore, AssignmentStore, BoundaryStore\",\n   353→   353→   353→        \"import(PolicyDocument $document, ImportOptions $options): ImportResult: If $options-\\u003evalidate is true, validate that permission strings referenced in roles exist in the document's permissions list or are already registered. Collect warnings for unregistered permissions. If $options-\\u003emerge is true (default), merge with existing state (create new, update existing, don't delete missing). If false, replace: remove all existing permissions/roles/assignments/boundaries before importing. If $options-\\u003edryRun is true, compute the result without writing to any store. Return the ImportResult showing what would change. If $options-\\u003eskipAssignments is true, skip importing assignments. Processing order: permissions first, then roles, then boundaries, then assignments. Register all permissions via PermissionStore::register(). Save all roles via RoleStore::save(). Set all boundaries via BoundaryStore::set(). Create all assignments via AssignmentStore::assign() (parse subject field as type::id). Dispatch DocumentImported event with the ImportResult. Return ImportResult with counts and warnings\",\n   354→   354→   354→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/DefaultDocumentImporterTest.php covering: full import, merge mode, replace mode, dry run (no DB changes), skip assignments, validation warnings, round-trip with exporter\"\n   355→   355→   355→      ],\n   356→   356→   356→      \"priority\": 21,\n   357→   357→   357→      \"passes\": false\n   358→   358→   358→    },\n   359→   359→   359→    {\n   360→   360→   360→      \"id\": \"US-022\",\n   361→   361→   361→      \"title\": \"Implement DefaultDocumentExporter\",\n   362→   362→   362→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a document exporter so the current authorization state can be exported as a PolicyDocument.\",\n   363→   363→   363→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   364→   364→   364→        \"src/Documents/DefaultDocumentExporter.php implements DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Contracts\\\\DocumentExporter\",\n   365→   365→   365→        \"Constructor accepts: PermissionStore, RoleStore, AssignmentStore, BoundaryStore\",\n   366→   366→   366→        \"export(?string $scope = null): PolicyDocument: If $scope is null, export everything: all permissions, all roles with their permissions, all assignments, all boundaries. If $scope is provided, export only: all permissions (always included), roles that have assignments in this scope, assignments in this scope, boundary for this scope (if exists). Build and return a PolicyDocument DTO with version = '1.0'. Assignments are serialized as subject = \\\"{type}::{id}\\\", role = role_id, scope = scope string or omitted if null\",\n   367→   367→   367→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/DefaultDocumentExporterTest.php covering: export all, export scoped, export empty state, round-trip with importer\"\n   368→   368→   368→      ],\n   369→   369→   369→      \"priority\": 22,\n   370→   370→   370→      \"passes\": false\n   371→   371→   371→    },\n   372→   372→   372→    {\n   373→   373→   373→      \"id\": \"US-023\",\n   374→   374→   374→      \"title\": \"Implement listing Artisan commands\",\n   375→   375→   375→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need Artisan commands to list permissions, roles, and assignments for inspection and debugging.\",\n   376→   376→   376→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   377→   377→   377→        \"src/Commands/ListPermissionsCommand.php — signature: primitives:permissions. Lists all registered permissions in a table format (ID, description). Resolves PermissionStore from container\",\n   378→   378→   378→        \"src/Commands/ListRolesCommand.php — signature: primitives:roles. Lists all roles in a table (ID, name, system flag, permission count). For each role, shows its permissions indented below\",\n   379→   379→   379→        \"src/Commands/ListAssignmentsCommand.php — signature: primitives:assignments {subject?} {--scope=}. If subject argument is provided, lists assignments for that subject (expects format type::id, e.g., user::42). If --scope option is provided, lists all assignments in that scope. If neither, shows usage help. Resolves AssignmentStore from container\",\n   380→   380→   380→        \"All commands are registered in the service provider\",\n   381→   381→   381→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: each command runs without error, output contains expected data\"\n   382→   382→   382→      ],\n   383→   383→   383→      \"priority\": 23,\n   384→   384→   384→      \"passes\": false\n   385→   385→   385→    },\n   386→   386→   386→    {\n   387→   387→   387→      \"id\": \"US-024\",\n   388→   388→   388→      \"title\": \"Implement explain Artisan command\",\n   389→   389→   389→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need an Artisan command to explain why a permission check passes or fails.\",\n   390→   390→   390→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   391→   391→   391→        \"src/Commands/ExplainCommand.php — signature: primitives:explain {subject} {permission} {--scope=}\",\n   392→   392→   392→        \"subject argument expects format type::id (e.g., user::42) — parse into subjectType and subjectId\",\n   393→   393→   393→        \"Delegates to Evaluator::explain(), building the full permission string with scope if --scope is provided\",\n   394→   394→   394→        \"Outputs the EvaluationTrace in a human-readable format: subject, required permission, result (ALLOW/DENY), each assignment checked with its role and which permissions matched/didn't match, boundary info, cache hit status\",\n   395→   395→   395→        \"If config('policy-engine.explain') is false, shows an error message telling the user to enable it\",\n   396→   396→   396→        \"Pest feature test in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: explain command output for allow and deny cases\"\n   397→   397→   397→      ],\n   398→   398→   398→      \"priority\": 24,\n   399→   399→   399→      \"passes\": false\n   400→   400→   400→    },\n   401→   401→   401→    {\n   402→   402→   402→      \"id\": \"US-025\",\n   403→   403→   403→      \"title\": \"Implement import Artisan command\",\n   404→   404→   404→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need an Artisan command to import policy documents from JSON files.\",\n   405→   405→   405→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   406→   406→   406→        \"src/Commands/ImportCommand.php — signature: primitives:import {path} {--dry-run} {--skip-assignments} {--replace} {--force}\",\n   407→   407→   407→        \"Reads the file at {path}, delegates to Primitives::import() with appropriate ImportOptions\",\n   408→   408→   408→        \"--dry-run: sets ImportOptions::dryRun = true, outputs what would change without applying\",\n   409→   409→   409→        \"--skip-assignments: sets ImportOptions::skipAssignments = true\",\n   410→   410→   410→        \"--replace: sets ImportOptions::merge = false. Requires --force flag or prompts for confirmation (\\\"This will delete all existing permissions, roles, assignments, and boundaries. Continue?\\\")\",\n   411→   411→   411→        \"Outputs a summary: permissions created, roles created/updated, assignments created, warnings\",\n   412→   412→   412→        \"If file not found, shows error message\",\n   413→   413→   413→        \"Pest feature test in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: import success, dry run output, file not found error\"\n   414→   414→   414→      ],\n   415→   415→   415→      \"priority\": 25,\n   416→   416→   416→      \"passes\": false\n   417→   417→   417→    },\n   418→   418→   418→    {\n   419→   419→   419→      \"id\": \"US-026\",\n   420→   420→   420→      \"title\": \"Implement export Artisan command\",\n   421→   421→   421→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need an Artisan command to export authorization state to JSON.\",\n   422→   422→   422→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   423→   423→   423→        \"src/Commands/ExportCommand.php — signature: primitives:export {--scope=} {--path=} {--stdout}\",\n   424→   424→   424→        \"If --path is provided, writes the JSON to that file path\",\n   425→   425→   425→        \"If --stdout is provided, outputs the JSON to stdout (useful for piping to jq)\",\n   426→   426→   426→        \"If neither --path nor --stdout, defaults to outputting to stdout\",\n   427→   427→   427→        \"If --scope is provided, passes it to Primitives::export(scope: $scope) for scoped export\",\n   428→   428→   428→        \"Pest feature test in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: export to stdout, export to file, export scoped\"\n   429→   429→   429→      ],\n   430→   430→   430→      \"priority\": 26,\n   431→   431→   431→      \"passes\": false\n   432→   432→   432→    },\n   433→   433→   433→    {\n   434→   434→   434→      \"id\": \"US-027\",\n   435→   435→   435→      \"title\": \"Implement validate Artisan command\",\n   436→   436→   436→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need an Artisan command to validate a policy document without importing it.\",\n   437→   437→   437→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   438→   438→   438→        \"src/Commands/ValidateCommand.php — signature: primitives:validate {path}\",\n   439→   439→   439→        \"Reads the file, delegates to DocumentParser::validate()\",\n   440→   440→   440→        \"If valid, outputs success message\",\n   441→   441→   441→        \"If invalid, outputs each validation error\",\n   442→   442→   442→        \"Exit code 0 on valid, 1 on invalid\",\n   443→   443→   443→        \"Pest feature test in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: validate valid file, validate invalid file\"\n   444→   444→   444→      ],\n   445→   445→   445→      \"priority\": 27,\n   446→   446→   446→      \"passes\": false\n   447→   447→   447→    },\n   448→   448→   448→    {\n   449→   449→   449→      \"id\": \"US-028\",\n   450→   450→   450→      \"title\": \"Implement sync and cache-clear Artisan commands\",\n   451→   451→   451→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need utility Artisan commands for syncing permissions and clearing cache.\",\n   452→   452→   452→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   453→   453→   453→        \"src/Commands/SyncCommand.php — signature: primitives:sync. Calls Artisan::call('db:seed', ['--class' =\\u003e 'PermissionSeeder']) or a configurable seeder class. Outputs success message. This re-runs the seeder idempotently\",\n   454→   454→   454→        \"src/Commands/CacheClearCommand.php — signature: primitives:cache-clear. Flushes all cache keys with the policy-engine: prefix. Uses the configured cache store from config('policy-engine.cache.store'). Outputs success message with count of cleared entries (or a generic \\\"Cache cleared\\\" if count is unavailable)\",\n   455→   455→   455→        \"Both commands are registered in the service provider\",\n   456→   456→   456→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: cache-clear runs without error\"\n   457→   457→   457→      ],\n   458→   458→   458→      \"priority\": 28,\n   459→   459→   459→      \"passes\": false\n   460→   460→   460→    },\n   461→   461→   461→    {\n   462→   462→   462→      \"id\": \"US-029\",\n   463→   463→   463→      \"title\": \"Wire service provider with all bindings\",\n   464→   464→   464→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the service provider to bind all contracts to default implementations and register all DX surfaces so the package works on install.\",\n   465→   465→   465→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   466→   466→   466→        \"register() method binds all contracts to default implementations: PermissionStore::class =\\u003e EloquentPermissionStore::class, RoleStore::class =\\u003e EloquentRoleStore::class, AssignmentStore::class =\\u003e EloquentAssignmentStore::class, BoundaryStore::class =\\u003e EloquentBoundaryStore::class, Matcher::class =\\u003e WildcardMatcher::class, ScopeResolver::class =\\u003e ModelScopeResolver::class, DocumentParser::class =\\u003e JsonDocumentParser::class, DocumentImporter::class =\\u003e DefaultDocumentImporter::class, DocumentExporter::class =\\u003e DefaultDocumentExporter::class, Evaluator::class =\\u003e CachedEvaluator::class (with DefaultEvaluator as the inner evaluator — use $this-\\u003eapp-\\u003ebind() with a closure that constructs CachedEvaluator wrapping DefaultEvaluator), PrimitivesManager::class as singleton\",\n   467→   467→   467→        \"boot() method: Publishes config: $this-\\u003epublishes([config_path =\\u003e config_path('policy-engine.php')], 'policy-engine-config'). Publishes migrations via $this-\\u003epublishesMigrations(). Loads migrations from package path. Registers middleware aliases: can_do =\\u003e CanDoMiddleware::class, role =\\u003e RoleMiddleware::class. Registers Blade directives: @canDo, @endCanDo, @cannotDo, @endCannotDo, @hasRole, @endHasRole. Registers Artisan commands (all 8 commands) when running in console. Registers event listeners for cache invalidation\",\n   468→   468→   468→        \"Merges config in register() via $this-\\u003emergeConfigFrom()\",\n   469→   469→   469→        \"Pest feature test: the service provider can be booted in a test Laravel app without errors, and all contracts resolve from the container\"\n   470→   470→   470→      ],\n   471→   471→   471→      \"priority\": 29,\n   472→   472→   472→      \"passes\": false\n   473→   473→   473→    },\n   474→   474→   474→    {\n   475→   475→   475→      \"id\": \"US-030\",\n   476→   476→   476→      \"title\": \"Implement Sanctum token scoping\",\n   477→   477→   477→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the evaluator to intersect Sanctum token abilities with role-based permissions so tokens can only exercise permissions they explicitly declare.\",\n   478→   478→   478→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   479→   479→   479→        \"In DefaultEvaluator::can(), after the normal evaluation resolves to true, check if the current request is authenticated via Sanctum (check if $user-\\u003ecurrentAccessToken() exists and is a Sanctum PersonalAccessToken)\",\n   480→   480→   480→        \"If a Sanctum token is present, get the token's abilities array\",\n   481→   481→   481→        \"The final result is true only if BOTH the role-based evaluation allows the permission AND the token's abilities include a matching permission (using the Matcher for wildcard support)\",\n   482→   482→   482→        \"If no Sanctum token is present (session auth, etc.), skip the token check — role-based result stands\",\n   483→   483→   483→        \"This behavior is in DefaultEvaluator so it flows through CachedEvaluator automatically\",\n   484→   484→   484→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/SanctumScopingTest.php covering: token with matching ability allows, token without matching ability denies, no token (session auth) allows normally. These tests should be skippable if Sanctum is not installed\"\n   485→   485→   485→      ],\n   486→   486→   486→      \"priority\": 30,\n   487→   487→   487→      \"passes\": false\n   488→   488→   488→    },\n   489→   489→   489→    {\n   490→   490→   490→      \"id\": \"US-031\",\n   491→   491→   491→      \"title\": \"Core feature tests — matching, evaluation, boundaries\",\n   492→   492→   492→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need comprehensive tests for the core evaluation pipeline to ensure correctness.\",\n   493→   493→   493→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   494→   494→   494→        \"tests/Feature/EvaluationPipelineTest.php — end-to-end tests that set up permissions, roles, assignments, and boundaries, then assert canDo() results. Tests should use the HasPermissions trait on a test User model and exercise the full stack (stores → evaluator → trait)\",\n   495→   495→   495→        \"Test case: User with member role can do posts.create (has permission)\",\n   496→   496→   496→        \"Test case: User with member role cannot do members.remove (lacks permission)\",\n   497→   497→   497→        \"Test case: User with moderator role with !posts.delete.any deny rule cannot delete (deny wins)\",\n   498→   498→   498→        \"Test case: User with admin role with *.* wildcard can do anything\",\n   499→   499→   499→        \"Test case: User with scoped assignment (group::5) can do permission in that scope\",\n   500→   500→   500→        \"Test case: User with scoped assignment cannot do permission in a different scope\",\n   501→   501→   501→        \"Test case: User with global assignment can do permission in any scope\",\n   502→   502→   502→        \"Test case: Boundary restricts: user has *.* but boundary on scope limits to posts.*, user cannot do members.invite in that scope\",\n   503→   503→   503→        \"Test case: Boundary allows: user has posts.create and boundary includes posts.*, user can do posts.create\",\n   504→   504→   504→        \"Test case: No assignment = deny\",\n   505→   505→   505→        \"All tests use Pest syntax with it() or test() blocks\",\n   506→   506→   506→        \"All tests use RefreshDatabase trait (or equivalent for package testing)\"\n   507→   507→   507→      ],\n   508→   508→   508→      \"priority\": 31,\n   509→   509→   509→      \"passes\": false\n   510→   510→   510→    },\n   511→   511→   511→    {\n   512→   512→   512→      \"id\": \"US-032\",\n   513→   513→   513→      \"title\": \"DX feature tests — middleware, blade, documents, commands\",\n   514→   514→   514→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need comprehensive tests for the DX layer to ensure all user-facing surfaces work correctly.\",\n   515→   515→   515→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   516→   516→   516→        \"tests/Feature/DocumentRoundTripTest.php — tests that create permissions/roles/assignments/boundaries, export to JSON, clear the database, import the JSON, and verify the state matches. Covers: full round-trip, scoped export/import, partial document import (roles only)\",\n   517→   517→   517→        \"tests/Feature/CacheInvalidationTest.php — tests that verify cache is invalidated when assignments change, roles change, or permissions are deleted. Verify that after invalidation, subsequent canDo() checks reflect the updated state\",\n   518→   518→   518→        \"All existing test files from prior stories should pass\",\n   519→   519→   519→        \"Run vendor/bin/pest — all tests pass with zero failures\"\n   520→   520→   520→      ],\n   521→   521→   521→      \"priority\": 32,\n   522→   522→   522→      \"passes\": false\n   523→   523→   523→    }\n   524→   524→   524→  ]\n   525→   525→   525→}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce4d2e8c-11e0-48e3-8ef5-8ea123e4d07a","uuid":"2c2c596f-2c03-4aff-b49a-240de2e10262","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisarter/.claude/projects/-Users-chrisarter-Documents-projects-policy-engine/ce4d2e8c-11e0-48e3-8ef5-8ea123e4d07a/tool-results/toolu_016BkXTRxGxrvqJbNU5sZbbC.txt","content":"   300→   300→      \"priority\": 17,\n   301→   301→      \"passes\": false\n   302→   302→    },\n   303→   303→    {\n   304→   304→      \"id\": \"US-018\",\n   305→   305→      \"title\": \"Implement middleware\",\n   306→   306→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need can_do and role middleware so routes can be protected with permission and role checks.\",\n   307→   307→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   308→   308→        \"src/Middleware/CanDoMiddleware.php — middleware class with handle(Request $request, Closure $next, string $permission, ?string $scopeParam = null). Gets the authenticated user via $request-\\u003euser(). If $scopeParam is provided, resolves the scope from route parameters: $request-\\u003eroute($scopeParam). The route parameter value will be a model (via route model binding) or a string — pass it through ScopeResolver. Calls $user-\\u003ecanDo($permission, scope: $resolvedScope). If denied, aborts with 403. If allowed, passes to $next\",\n   309→   309→        \"src/Middleware/RoleMiddleware.php — middleware class with handle(Request $request, Closure $next, string $role, ?string $scopeParam = null). Gets the authenticated user. Resolves scope same as CanDoMiddleware. Checks if user has the required role in scope by querying AssignmentStore::forSubjectInScope() (or forSubject() if no scope) and checking if any assignment has the required role_id. If no matching assignment, aborts with 403. If found, passes to $next\",\n   310→   310→        \"Both middleware are registered in the service provider with aliases can_do and role\",\n   311→   311→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/MiddlewareTest.php covering: can_do allows, can_do denies (403), can_do with scope parameter, role allows, role denies (403), unauthenticated user (401 or redirect)\"\n   312→   312→      ],\n   313→   313→      \"priority\": 18,\n   314→   314→      \"passes\": false\n   315→   315→    },\n   316→   316→    {\n   317→   317→      \"id\": \"US-019\",\n   318→   318→      \"title\": \"Implement Blade directives\",\n   319→   319→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need Blade directives so views can conditionally render based on permissions and roles.\",\n   320→   320→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   321→   321→        \"@canDo('permission', $scope) / @endCanDo — compiles to a PHP if-block that calls auth()-\\u003euser()-\\u003ecanDo('permission', $scope). The second argument ($scope) is optional\",\n   322→   322→        \"@cannotDo('permission', $scope) / @endCannotDo — compiles to the negation\",\n   323→   323→        \"@hasRole('role', $scope) / @endHasRole — compiles to check if the user has the role assignment in the given scope. Uses AssignmentStore to check\",\n   324→   324→        \"Directives are registered in the service provider's boot() method via Blade::if()\",\n   325→   325→        \"If no user is authenticated, all directives evaluate to false (never throws)\",\n   326→   326→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/BladeDirectivesTest.php covering: canDo renders content when allowed, canDo hides content when denied, cannotDo inverse behavior, hasRole with and without scope, unauthenticated user sees nothing\"\n   327→   327→      ],\n   328→   328→      \"priority\": 19,\n   329→   329→      \"passes\": false\n   330→   330→    },\n   331→   331→    {\n   332→   332→      \"id\": \"US-020\",\n   333→   333→      \"title\": \"Implement JsonDocumentParser\",\n   334→   334→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a JSON document parser so policy documents can be parsed from and serialized to JSON strings.\",\n   335→   335→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   336→   336→        \"src/Documents/JsonDocumentParser.php implements DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Contracts\\\\DocumentParser\",\n   337→   337→        \"parse(string $content): PolicyDocument — decodes JSON string, validates structure, returns a PolicyDocument DTO. Throws \\\\InvalidArgumentException if JSON is invalid\",\n   338→   338→        \"serialize(PolicyDocument $document): string — encodes the DTO to a pretty-printed JSON string (JSON_PRETTY_PRINT | JSON_UNESCAPED_SLASHES)\",\n   339→   339→        \"validate(string $content): ValidationResult — validates JSON structure without importing. Checks: valid JSON, version field exists, permissions is array of strings (if present), roles entries have id, name, permissions keys (if present), assignments entries have subject and role keys (if present), boundaries entries have scope and max_permissions keys (if present). Returns ValidationResult with valid = true or valid = false with error messages\",\n   340→   340→        \"All sections of the document (permissions, roles, assignments, boundaries) are optional — a document with only roles is valid\",\n   341→   341→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/JsonDocumentParserTest.php covering: parse valid document, parse partial document (roles only), parse invalid JSON, serialize round-trip, validate valid document, validate invalid document\"\n   342→   342→      ],\n   343→   343→      \"priority\": 20,\n   344→   344→      \"passes\": false\n   345→   345→    },\n   346→   346→    {\n   347→   347→      \"id\": \"US-021\",\n   348→   348→      \"title\": \"Implement DefaultDocumentImporter\",\n   349→   349→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a document importer so parsed policy documents can be applied to the stores.\",\n   350→   350→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   351→   351→        \"src/Documents/DefaultDocumentImporter.php implements DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Contracts\\\\DocumentImporter\",\n   352→   352→        \"Constructor accepts: PermissionStore, RoleStore, AssignmentStore, BoundaryStore\",\n   353→   353→        \"import(PolicyDocument $document, ImportOptions $options): ImportResult: If $options-\\u003evalidate is true, validate that permission strings referenced in roles exist in the document's permissions list or are already registered. Collect warnings for unregistered permissions. If $options-\\u003emerge is true (default), merge with existing state (create new, update existing, don't delete missing). If false, replace: remove all existing permissions/roles/assignments/boundaries before importing. If $options-\\u003edryRun is true, compute the result without writing to any store. Return the ImportResult showing what would change. If $options-\\u003eskipAssignments is true, skip importing assignments. Processing order: permissions first, then roles, then boundaries, then assignments. Register all permissions via PermissionStore::register(). Save all roles via RoleStore::save(). Set all boundaries via BoundaryStore::set(). Create all assignments via AssignmentStore::assign() (parse subject field as type::id). Dispatch DocumentImported event with the ImportResult. Return ImportResult with counts and warnings\",\n   354→   354→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/DefaultDocumentImporterTest.php covering: full import, merge mode, replace mode, dry run (no DB changes), skip assignments, validation warnings, round-trip with exporter\"\n   355→   355→      ],\n   356→   356→      \"priority\": 21,\n   357→   357→      \"passes\": false\n   358→   358→    },\n   359→   359→    {\n   360→   360→      \"id\": \"US-022\",\n   361→   361→      \"title\": \"Implement DefaultDocumentExporter\",\n   362→   362→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a document exporter so the current authorization state can be exported as a PolicyDocument.\",\n   363→   363→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   364→   364→        \"src/Documents/DefaultDocumentExporter.php implements DynamikDev\\\\PolicyEngine\\\\Contracts\\\\DocumentExporter\",\n   365→   365→        \"Constructor accepts: PermissionStore, RoleStore, AssignmentStore, BoundaryStore\",\n   366→   366→        \"export(?string $scope = null): PolicyDocument: If $scope is null, export everything: all permissions, all roles with their permissions, all assignments, all boundaries. If $scope is provided, export only: all permissions (always included), roles that have assignments in this scope, assignments in this scope, boundary for this scope (if exists). Build and return a PolicyDocument DTO with version = '1.0'. Assignments are serialized as subject = \\\"{type}::{id}\\\", role = role_id, scope = scope string or omitted if null\",\n   367→   367→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/DefaultDocumentExporterTest.php covering: export all, export scoped, export empty state, round-trip with importer\"\n   368→   368→      ],\n   369→   369→      \"priority\": 22,\n   370→   370→      \"passes\": false\n   371→   371→    },\n   372→   372→    {\n   373→   373→      \"id\": \"US-023\",\n   374→   374→      \"title\": \"Implement listing Artisan commands\",\n   375→   375→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need Artisan commands to list permissions, roles, and assignments for inspection and debugging.\",\n   376→   376→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   377→   377→        \"src/Commands/ListPermissionsCommand.php — signature: primitives:permissions. Lists all registered permissions in a table format (ID, description). Resolves PermissionStore from container\",\n   378→   378→        \"src/Commands/ListRolesCommand.php — signature: primitives:roles. Lists all roles in a table (ID, name, system flag, permission count). For each role, shows its permissions indented below\",\n   379→   379→        \"src/Commands/ListAssignmentsCommand.php — signature: primitives:assignments {subject?} {--scope=}. If subject argument is provided, lists assignments for that subject (expects format type::id, e.g., user::42). If --scope option is provided, lists all assignments in that scope. If neither, shows usage help. Resolves AssignmentStore from container\",\n   380→   380→        \"All commands are registered in the service provider\",\n   381→   381→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: each command runs without error, output contains expected data\"\n   382→   382→      ],\n   383→   383→      \"priority\": 23,\n   384→   384→      \"passes\": false\n   385→   385→    },\n   386→   386→    {\n   387→   387→      \"id\": \"US-024\",\n   388→   388→      \"title\": \"Implement explain Artisan command\",\n   389→   389→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need an Artisan command to explain why a permission check passes or fails.\",\n   390→   390→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   391→   391→        \"src/Commands/ExplainCommand.php — signature: primitives:explain {subject} {permission} {--scope=}\",\n   392→   392→        \"subject argument expects format type::id (e.g., user::42) — parse into subjectType and subjectId\",\n   393→   393→        \"Delegates to Evaluator::explain(), building the full permission string with scope if --scope is provided\",\n   394→   394→        \"Outputs the EvaluationTrace in a human-readable format: subject, required permission, result (ALLOW/DENY), each assignment checked with its role and which permissions matched/didn't match, boundary info, cache hit status\",\n   395→   395→        \"If config('policy-engine.explain') is false, shows an error message telling the user to enable it\",\n   396→   396→        \"Pest feature test in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: explain command output for allow and deny cases\"\n   397→   397→      ],\n   398→   398→      \"priority\": 24,\n   399→   399→      \"passes\": false\n   400→   400→    },\n   401→   401→    {\n   402→   402→      \"id\": \"US-025\",\n   403→   403→      \"title\": \"Implement import Artisan command\",\n   404→   404→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need an Artisan command to import policy documents from JSON files.\",\n   405→   405→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   406→   406→        \"src/Commands/ImportCommand.php — signature: primitives:import {path} {--dry-run} {--skip-assignments} {--replace} {--force}\",\n   407→   407→        \"Reads the file at {path}, delegates to Primitives::import() with appropriate ImportOptions\",\n   408→   408→        \"--dry-run: sets ImportOptions::dryRun = true, outputs what would change without applying\",\n   409→   409→        \"--skip-assignments: sets ImportOptions::skipAssignments = true\",\n   410→   410→        \"--replace: sets ImportOptions::merge = false. Requires --force flag or prompts for confirmation (\\\"This will delete all existing permissions, roles, assignments, and boundaries. Continue?\\\")\",\n   411→   411→        \"Outputs a summary: permissions created, roles created/updated, assignments created, warnings\",\n   412→   412→        \"If file not found, shows error message\",\n   413→   413→        \"Pest feature test in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: import success, dry run output, file not found error\"\n   414→   414→      ],\n   415→   415→      \"priority\": 25,\n   416→   416→      \"passes\": false\n   417→   417→    },\n   418→   418→    {\n   419→   419→      \"id\": \"US-026\",\n   420→   420→      \"title\": \"Implement export Artisan command\",\n   421→   421→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need an Artisan command to export authorization state to JSON.\",\n   422→   422→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   423→   423→        \"src/Commands/ExportCommand.php — signature: primitives:export {--scope=} {--path=} {--stdout}\",\n   424→   424→        \"If --path is provided, writes the JSON to that file path\",\n   425→   425→        \"If --stdout is provided, outputs the JSON to stdout (useful for piping to jq)\",\n   426→   426→        \"If neither --path nor --stdout, defaults to outputting to stdout\",\n   427→   427→        \"If --scope is provided, passes it to Primitives::export(scope: $scope) for scoped export\",\n   428→   428→        \"Pest feature test in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: export to stdout, export to file, export scoped\"\n   429→   429→      ],\n   430→   430→      \"priority\": 26,\n   431→   431→      \"passes\": false\n   432→   432→    },\n   433→   433→    {\n   434→   434→      \"id\": \"US-027\",\n   435→   435→      \"title\": \"Implement validate Artisan command\",\n   436→   436→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need an Artisan command to validate a policy document without importing it.\",\n   437→   437→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   438→   438→        \"src/Commands/ValidateCommand.php — signature: primitives:validate {path}\",\n   439→   439→        \"Reads the file, delegates to DocumentParser::validate()\",\n   440→   440→        \"If valid, outputs success message\",\n   441→   441→        \"If invalid, outputs each validation error\",\n   442→   442→        \"Exit code 0 on valid, 1 on invalid\",\n   443→   443→        \"Pest feature test in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: validate valid file, validate invalid file\"\n   444→   444→      ],\n   445→   445→      \"priority\": 27,\n   446→   446→      \"passes\": false\n   447→   447→    },\n   448→   448→    {\n   449→   449→      \"id\": \"US-028\",\n   450→   450→      \"title\": \"Implement sync and cache-clear Artisan commands\",\n   451→   451→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need utility Artisan commands for syncing permissions and clearing cache.\",\n   452→   452→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   453→   453→        \"src/Commands/SyncCommand.php — signature: primitives:sync. Calls Artisan::call('db:seed', ['--class' =\\u003e 'PermissionSeeder']) or a configurable seeder class. Outputs success message. This re-runs the seeder idempotently\",\n   454→   454→        \"src/Commands/CacheClearCommand.php — signature: primitives:cache-clear. Flushes all cache keys with the policy-engine: prefix. Uses the configured cache store from config('policy-engine.cache.store'). Outputs success message with count of cleared entries (or a generic \\\"Cache cleared\\\" if count is unavailable)\",\n   455→   455→        \"Both commands are registered in the service provider\",\n   456→   456→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/ArtisanCommandsTest.php covering: cache-clear runs without error\"\n   457→   457→      ],\n   458→   458→      \"priority\": 28,\n   459→   459→      \"passes\": false\n   460→   460→    },\n   461→   461→    {\n   462→   462→      \"id\": \"US-029\",\n   463→   463→      \"title\": \"Wire service provider with all bindings\",\n   464→   464→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the service provider to bind all contracts to default implementations and register all DX surfaces so the package works on install.\",\n   465→   465→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   466→   466→        \"register() method binds all contracts to default implementations: PermissionStore::class =\\u003e EloquentPermissionStore::class, RoleStore::class =\\u003e EloquentRoleStore::class, AssignmentStore::class =\\u003e EloquentAssignmentStore::class, BoundaryStore::class =\\u003e EloquentBoundaryStore::class, Matcher::class =\\u003e WildcardMatcher::class, ScopeResolver::class =\\u003e ModelScopeResolver::class, DocumentParser::class =\\u003e JsonDocumentParser::class, DocumentImporter::class =\\u003e DefaultDocumentImporter::class, DocumentExporter::class =\\u003e DefaultDocumentExporter::class, Evaluator::class =\\u003e CachedEvaluator::class (with DefaultEvaluator as the inner evaluator — use $this-\\u003eapp-\\u003ebind() with a closure that constructs CachedEvaluator wrapping DefaultEvaluator), PrimitivesManager::class as singleton\",\n   467→   467→        \"boot() method: Publishes config: $this-\\u003epublishes([config_path =\\u003e config_path('policy-engine.php')], 'policy-engine-config'). Publishes migrations via $this-\\u003epublishesMigrations(). Loads migrations from package path. Registers middleware aliases: can_do =\\u003e CanDoMiddleware::class, role =\\u003e RoleMiddleware::class. Registers Blade directives: @canDo, @endCanDo, @cannotDo, @endCannotDo, @hasRole, @endHasRole. Registers Artisan commands (all 8 commands) when running in console. Registers event listeners for cache invalidation\",\n   468→   468→        \"Merges config in register() via $this-\\u003emergeConfigFrom()\",\n   469→   469→        \"Pest feature test: the service provider can be booted in a test Laravel app without errors, and all contracts resolve from the container\"\n   470→   470→      ],\n   471→   471→      \"priority\": 29,\n   472→   472→      \"passes\": false\n   473→   473→    },\n   474→   474→    {\n   475→   475→      \"id\": \"US-030\",\n   476→   476→      \"title\": \"Implement Sanctum token scoping\",\n   477→   477→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the evaluator to intersect Sanctum token abilities with role-based permissions so tokens can only exercise permissions they explicitly declare.\",\n   478→   478→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   479→   479→        \"In DefaultEvaluator::can(), after the normal evaluation resolves to true, check if the current request is authenticated via Sanctum (check if $user-\\u003ecurrentAccessToken() exists and is a Sanctum PersonalAccessToken)\",\n   480→   480→        \"If a Sanctum token is present, get the token's abilities array\",\n   481→   481→        \"The final result is true only if BOTH the role-based evaluation allows the permission AND the token's abilities include a matching permission (using the Matcher for wildcard support)\",\n   482→   482→        \"If no Sanctum token is present (session auth, etc.), skip the token check — role-based result stands\",\n   483→   483→        \"This behavior is in DefaultEvaluator so it flows through CachedEvaluator automatically\",\n   484→   484→        \"Pest feature tests in tests/Feature/SanctumScopingTest.php covering: token with matching ability allows, token without matching ability denies, no token (session auth) allows normally. These tests should be skippable if Sanctum is not installed\"\n   485→   485→      ],\n   486→   486→      \"priority\": 30,\n   487→   487→      \"passes\": false\n   488→   488→    },\n   489→   489→    {\n   490→   490→      \"id\": \"US-031\",\n   491→   491→      \"title\": \"Core feature tests — matching, evaluation, boundaries\",\n   492→   492→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need comprehensive tests for the core evaluation pipeline to ensure correctness.\",\n   493→   493→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   494→   494→        \"tests/Feature/EvaluationPipelineTest.php — end-to-end tests that set up permissions, roles, assignments, and boundaries, then assert canDo() results. Tests should use the HasPermissions trait on a test User model and exercise the full stack (stores → evaluator → trait)\",\n   495→   495→        \"Test case: User with member role can do posts.create (has permission)\",\n   496→   496→        \"Test case: User with member role cannot do members.remove (lacks permission)\",\n   497→   497→        \"Test case: User with moderator role with !posts.delete.any deny rule cannot delete (deny wins)\",\n   498→   498→        \"Test case: User with admin role with *.* wildcard can do anything\",\n   499→   499→        \"Test case: User with scoped assignment (group::5) can do permission in that scope\",\n   500→   500→        \"Test case: User with scoped assignment cannot do permission in a different scope\",\n   501→   501→        \"Test case: User with global assignment can do permission in any scope\",\n   502→   502→        \"Test case: Boundary restricts: user has *.* but boundary on scope limits to posts.*, user cannot do members.invite in that scope\",\n   503→   503→        \"Test case: Boundary allows: user has posts.create and boundary includes posts.*, user can do posts.create\",\n   504→   504→        \"Test case: No assignment = deny\",\n   505→   505→        \"All tests use Pest syntax with it() or test() blocks\",\n   506→   506→        \"All tests use RefreshDatabase trait (or equivalent for package testing)\"\n   507→   507→      ],\n   508→   508→      \"priority\": 31,\n   509→   509→      \"passes\": false\n   510→   510→    },\n   511→   511→    {\n   512→   512→      \"id\": \"US-032\",\n   513→   513→      \"title\": \"DX feature tests — middleware, blade, documents, commands\",\n   514→   514→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need comprehensive tests for the DX layer to ensure all user-facing surfaces work correctly.\",\n   515→   515→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   516→   516→        \"tests/Feature/DocumentRoundTripTest.php — tests that create permissions/roles/assignments/boundaries, export to JSON, clear the database, import the JSON, and verify the state matches. Covers: full round-trip, scoped export/import, partial document import (roles only)\",\n   517→   517→        \"tests/Feature/CacheInvalidationTest.php — tests that verify cache is invalidated when assignments change, roles change, or permissions are deleted. Verify that after invalidation, subsequent canDo() checks reflect the updated state\",\n   518→   518→        \"All existing test files from prior stories should pass\",\n   519→   519→        \"Run vendor/bin/pest — all tests pass with zero failures\"\n   520→   520→      ],\n   521→   521→      \"priority\": 32,\n   522→   522→      \"passes\": false\n   523→   523→    }\n   524→   524→  ]\n   525→   525→}","numLines":226,"startLine":300,"totalLines":525}}}
