{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VmHEBRqqRDGgVuBS9VK2iq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QthMt2vfnYoL6TihTPiTjx","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Create database migrations","subagent_type":"laravel-eloquent-expert","prompt":"Create the database migrations for the Laravel Policy Engine package at `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/`.\n\nThe migrations should go in `database/migrations/` directory. All migrations MUST use anonymous classes (`return new class extends Migration`).\n\nCreate these migration files (use the naming convention with a sequential prefix for ordering):\n\n1. **`database/migrations/create_permissions_table.php`**:\n   - `permissions` table with `string('id')->primary()`, nullable `string('description')`, `timestamps()`\n\n2. **`database/migrations/create_roles_table.php`**:\n   - `roles` table with `string('id')->primary()`, `string('name')`, `boolean('is_system')->default(false)`, `timestamps()`\n\n3. **`database/migrations/create_role_permissions_table.php`**:\n   - `role_permissions` table with `string('role_id')`, `string('permission_id')`, composite `primary(['role_id', 'permission_id'])`, foreign key `role_id` referencing `roles.id` with cascade on delete\n\n4. **`database/migrations/create_assignments_table.php`**:\n   - `assignments` table with `id()` (auto-increment PK), `morphs('subject')` (creates `subject_type` and `subject_id`), `string('role_id')`, nullable `string('scope')`, `timestamps()`, unique constraint on `['subject_id', 'subject_type', 'role_id', 'scope']`, foreign key `role_id` referencing `roles.id` with cascade on delete, index on `scope`\n\n5. **`database/migrations/create_boundaries_table.php`**:\n   - `boundaries` table with `id()`, `string('scope')->unique()`, `json('max_permissions')`, `timestamps()`\n\nThen update the service provider at `src/PolicyEngineServiceProvider.php` to:\n- Load migrations in boot() using `$this->loadMigrationsFrom(__DIR__ . '/../database/migrations')`\n- Publish migrations using `$this->publishesMigrations()` — NOTE: This is NOT `$this->publishes()` for migrations. Use the Laravel `publishesMigrations()` method which was added in Laravel 11.\n\nSTYLE RULES (mandatory):\n- All files use `declare(strict_types=1)`\n- Anonymous migration classes (`return new class extends Migration`)\n- No `DB::` facade usage\n- Full PHP 8.4+ type hints and return types\n\nWrite the actual files. Do NOT just describe them."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":218,"cache_read_input_tokens":50524,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":218},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce4d2e8c-11e0-48e3-8ef5-8ea123e4d07a","uuid":"893b6519-d151-4f02-a397-06330142860f"}
