{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QthMt2vfnYoL6TihTPiTjx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here is a summary of everything that was created and modified.\n\n---\n\n## Files Created\n\n### 1. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_permissions_table.php`\n- `permissions` table with `string('id')->primary()`, nullable `description`, and timestamps.\n\n### 2. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_roles_table.php`\n- `roles` table with `string('id')->primary()`, `name`, `is_system` boolean defaulting to `false`, and timestamps.\n\n### 3. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_role_permissions_table.php`\n- `role_permissions` pivot table with `role_id` and `permission_id` string columns, composite primary key on both, and a foreign key on `role_id` referencing `roles.id` with cascade on delete.\n\n### 4. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_assignments_table.php`\n- `assignments` table with auto-increment `id()`, polymorphic `morphs('subject')`, `role_id` string, nullable `scope`, timestamps, a unique constraint on `['subject_id', 'subject_type', 'role_id', 'scope']`, foreign key on `role_id` with cascade delete, and an index on `scope`.\n\n### 5. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_boundaries_table.php`\n- `boundaries` table with auto-increment `id()`, unique `scope` string, `max_permissions` JSON column, and timestamps.\n\n## File Modified\n\n### `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/src/PolicyEngineServiceProvider.php`\n\nTwo additions to `boot()`:\n\n```php\npublic function boot(): void\n{\n    $this->loadMigrationsFrom(__DIR__.'/../database/migrations');\n\n    if ($this->app->runningInConsole()) {\n        $this->publishes([\n            __DIR__.'/../config/policy-engine.php' => config_path('policy-engine.php'),\n        ], 'policy-engine-config');\n\n        $this->publishesMigrations([\n            __DIR__.'/../database/migrations' => database_path('migrations'),\n        ], 'policy-engine-migrations');\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- `loadMigrationsFrom()` runs unconditionally so the package's migrations are always discovered by Laravel.\n- `publishesMigrations()` (Laravel 11+ method) allows users to publish with `php artisan vendor:publish --tag=policy-engine-migrations`, automatically prepending timestamps to the filenames so they sort correctly alongside application migrations.\n\nAll migrations use `declare(strict_types=1)`, anonymous classes, full return types, and were formatted with Pint."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a67973a0caabe1de9 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31856\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 76997</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ce4d2e8c-11e0-48e3-8ef5-8ea123e4d07a","uuid":"e0cab516-9023-467b-a3e9-2b3fe1b9bd76","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Create the database migrations for the Laravel Policy Engine package at `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/`.\n\nThe migrations should go in `database/migrations/` directory. All migrations MUST use anonymous classes (`return new class extends Migration`).\n\nCreate these migration files (use the naming convention with a sequential prefix for ordering):\n\n1. **`database/migrations/create_permissions_table.php`**:\n   - `permissions` table with `string('id')->primary()`, nullable `string('description')`, `timestamps()`\n\n2. **`database/migrations/create_roles_table.php`**:\n   - `roles` table with `string('id')->primary()`, `string('name')`, `boolean('is_system')->default(false)`, `timestamps()`\n\n3. **`database/migrations/create_role_permissions_table.php`**:\n   - `role_permissions` table with `string('role_id')`, `string('permission_id')`, composite `primary(['role_id', 'permission_id'])`, foreign key `role_id` referencing `roles.id` with cascade on delete\n\n4. **`database/migrations/create_assignments_table.php`**:\n   - `assignments` table with `id()` (auto-increment PK), `morphs('subject')` (creates `subject_type` and `subject_id`), `string('role_id')`, nullable `string('scope')`, `timestamps()`, unique constraint on `['subject_id', 'subject_type', 'role_id', 'scope']`, foreign key `role_id` referencing `roles.id` with cascade on delete, index on `scope`\n\n5. **`database/migrations/create_boundaries_table.php`**:\n   - `boundaries` table with `id()`, `string('scope')->unique()`, `json('max_permissions')`, `timestamps()`\n\nThen update the service provider at `src/PolicyEngineServiceProvider.php` to:\n- Load migrations in boot() using `$this->loadMigrationsFrom(__DIR__ . '/../database/migrations')`\n- Publish migrations using `$this->publishesMigrations()` — NOTE: This is NOT `$this->publishes()` for migrations. Use the Laravel `publishesMigrations()` method which was added in Laravel 11.\n\nSTYLE RULES (mandatory):\n- All files use `declare(strict_types=1)`\n- Anonymous migration classes (`return new class extends Migration`)\n- No `DB::` facade usage\n- Full PHP 8.4+ type hints and return types\n\nWrite the actual files. Do NOT just describe them.","agentId":"a67973a0caabe1de9","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here is a summary of everything that was created and modified.\n\n---\n\n## Files Created\n\n### 1. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_permissions_table.php`\n- `permissions` table with `string('id')->primary()`, nullable `description`, and timestamps.\n\n### 2. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_roles_table.php`\n- `roles` table with `string('id')->primary()`, `name`, `is_system` boolean defaulting to `false`, and timestamps.\n\n### 3. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_role_permissions_table.php`\n- `role_permissions` pivot table with `role_id` and `permission_id` string columns, composite primary key on both, and a foreign key on `role_id` referencing `roles.id` with cascade on delete.\n\n### 4. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_assignments_table.php`\n- `assignments` table with auto-increment `id()`, polymorphic `morphs('subject')`, `role_id` string, nullable `scope`, timestamps, a unique constraint on `['subject_id', 'subject_type', 'role_id', 'scope']`, foreign key on `role_id` with cascade delete, and an index on `scope`.\n\n### 5. `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/database/migrations/create_boundaries_table.php`\n- `boundaries` table with auto-increment `id()`, unique `scope` string, `max_permissions` JSON column, and timestamps.\n\n## File Modified\n\n### `/Users/chrisarter/Documents/projects/policy-engine/src/PolicyEngineServiceProvider.php`\n\nTwo additions to `boot()`:\n\n```php\npublic function boot(): void\n{\n    $this->loadMigrationsFrom(__DIR__.'/../database/migrations');\n\n    if ($this->app->runningInConsole()) {\n        $this->publishes([\n            __DIR__.'/../config/policy-engine.php' => config_path('policy-engine.php'),\n        ], 'policy-engine-config');\n\n        $this->publishesMigrations([\n            __DIR__.'/../database/migrations' => database_path('migrations'),\n        ], 'policy-engine-migrations');\n    }\n}\n```\n\n- `loadMigrationsFrom()` runs unconditionally so the package's migrations are always discovered by Laravel.\n- `publishesMigrations()` (Laravel 11+ method) allows users to publish with `php artisan vendor:publish --tag=policy-engine-migrations`, automatically prepending timestamps to the filenames so they sort correctly alongside application migrations.\n\nAll migrations use `declare(strict_types=1)`, anonymous classes, full return types, and were formatted with Pint."}],"totalDurationMs":76997,"totalTokens":31856,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":589,"cache_read_input_tokens":30571,"output_tokens":695,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":589,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
